prompt.content:
Please fill the dataset card for the UDPOS dataset. You can use the following schema:
languages: 
- "List of ISO 639-1 code for languages covered in the dataset"
- lang1
- lang2
...
- langM
pretty_name: "Pretty Name of the Dataset"
tags:
- tag1
- tag2
dataset_info:
    features:
        - name: "name of the feature1"
          dtype: "dtype of the feature1"
        ...
        - name: "name of the featureN"
          dtype: "dtype of the featureN"
    splits:
        train:
            num_examples: "number of examples in the train split"
        validation:
            num_examples: "number of examples in the validation split"
        test:
            num_examples: "number of examples in the test split"
dataset_summary: "Summary of the dataset's description"

response:
languages:
- "en"
- "fr"
- "de"
- "es"
- "it"
- "nl"
- "pt"
- "sv"
- "ru"
- "ar"
- "zh"
- "ja"
- "ko"
pretty_name: "Universal Dependencies Part-of-Speech Tagging (UDPOS)"
tags:
- "linguistics"
- "part-of-speech tagging"
- "multilingual"
dataset_info:
    features:
        - name: "id"
          dtype: "int32"
        - name: "form"
          dtype: "string"
        - name: "lemma"
          dtype: "string"
        - name: "upos"
          dtype: "string"
        - name: "xpos"
          dtype: "string"
        - name: "feats"
          dtype: "string"
        - name: "head"
          dtype: "int32"
        - name: "deprel"
          dtype: "string"
        - name: "deps"
          dtype: "string"
        - name: "misc"
          dtype: "string"
    splits:
        train:
            num_examples: 12543
        validation:
            num_examples: 2002
        test:
            num_examples: 2077
dataset_summary: "The Universal Dependencies Part-of-Speech Tagging (UDPOS) dataset is a collection of part-of-speech tagged sentences in multiple languages. It is designed to be a multilingual resource for natural language processing tasks such as machine translation, named entity recognition, and sentiment analysis."
